WEBVTT

00:03.786 --> 00:04.178
.

00:04.221 --> 00:06.223
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:06.267 --> 00:07.790
sexually based offenses

00:07.833 --> 00:09.574
are considered
especially heinous.

00:09.618 --> 00:11.663
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:11.707 --> 00:13.491
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:13.535 --> 00:15.145
are members of an elite squad

00:15.189 --> 00:17.060
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:17.104 --> 00:19.802
These are their stories.

00:20.629 --> 00:22.935
- Notice your breath
as it flows gently

00:22.979 --> 00:25.242
in and out of your body.

00:25.286 --> 00:28.550
Let your chest rise
and fall...

00:28.593 --> 00:32.162
[distant indistinct shouting]

00:32.206 --> 00:33.859
- Are you kidding me?

00:33.903 --> 00:35.383
- If your thoughts wander,

00:35.426 --> 00:38.212
simply refocus your mind on
your breathing.

00:38.255 --> 00:41.215
[shouting continues]

00:41.258 --> 00:44.131
[tranquil music]

00:44.174 --> 00:46.133
- Namaste my ass.

00:46.176 --> 00:49.049
[shouting continues]

00:49.092 --> 00:53.140
- What the hell are you doing?
I can hear you in here!

00:53.183 --> 00:54.706
- No, you're so annoying!

00:54.750 --> 00:56.665
- Look, we have rules,
Mackenzie, you know that!

00:56.708 --> 00:58.232
- Well, I don't need rules.
They're stupid!

00:58.275 --> 01:00.147
- Hey! You're not going
to have this!

01:00.190 --> 01:02.149
- If Mom were here--
- She is not here! I am!

01:02.192 --> 01:03.976
- I'll give you no Snapchat,
but my phone?

01:04.020 --> 01:05.587
- You lost the privilege, okay?

01:05.630 --> 01:07.371
And it's not coming back!
What are you doing?

01:07.415 --> 01:08.633
- Cook your own dinner!

01:08.677 --> 01:10.157
- Do not throw that!
[glass shatters]

01:10.200 --> 01:12.115
- I hate you!
You're so annoying!

01:12.159 --> 01:13.682
- God damn it!

01:13.725 --> 01:15.336
- Are you serious?
Look at what you did!

01:15.379 --> 01:17.947
- Stop, stop!
[screams]

01:17.990 --> 01:20.384
[tense music]

01:20.428 --> 01:23.692
- [sighs]
It's nothing really.

01:23.735 --> 01:25.302
- Well, that's not what
your neighbor says.

01:25.346 --> 01:26.738
- Yeah, well,
she's a nosy bitch,

01:26.782 --> 01:28.566
always butting in
where she's not wanted.

01:28.610 --> 01:31.221
- That's enough.
- Are you going to arrest us?

01:31.265 --> 01:33.136
- It--it's just
a big misunderstanding.

01:33.180 --> 01:36.313
- A lot of blood and broken
glass for a misunderstanding.

01:36.357 --> 01:38.054
- If you just let me
call Chase.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.316
- Did he hit you?

01:39.360 --> 01:41.753
- I don't know.
Can I have my phone back?

01:45.061 --> 01:46.410
- Garrett Howard and
his step-daughter,

01:46.454 --> 01:47.890
Mackenzie Tolliver, 13.

01:47.933 --> 01:50.110
Neighbor said she was screaming
bloody murder.

01:50.153 --> 01:52.068
- Where's Mom?
- I didn't think to ask.

01:52.112 --> 01:53.374
It's more up your alley
anyway.

01:53.417 --> 01:54.549
- You suspect child abuse?

01:54.592 --> 01:55.898
- There was evidence
of a fight.

01:55.941 --> 01:57.247
She wouldn't say
if she was hurt

01:57.291 --> 01:58.814
and Dad cut himself on
some glass.

01:58.857 --> 02:00.772
Figured I'd bring 'em both
here to get checked out.

02:00.816 --> 02:02.948
- Okay, we'll take it
from here.

02:02.992 --> 02:04.776
Mr. Howard, Mackenzie.

02:04.820 --> 02:08.128
I'm Lieutenant Benson.
Uh, this is Detective Carisi.

02:08.171 --> 02:09.738
- What do you want?

02:09.781 --> 02:12.523
- Mr. Howard, why do--why don't
you come talk to me over here?

02:14.917 --> 02:16.397
- So Mackenzie--

02:16.440 --> 02:18.573
- Lieutenant,
you saved me a call.

02:18.616 --> 02:20.401
If you have a minute.
- Okay.

02:20.444 --> 02:22.838
Give me a moment.
I'll be right back.

02:24.231 --> 02:25.449
What's going on?

02:25.493 --> 02:26.450
- I think we may have
a problem.

02:26.494 --> 02:27.973
- What kind of problem?

02:28.017 --> 02:29.366
- The girl was pretty
hysterical when she came in.

02:29.410 --> 02:31.063
- Okay, did she say
what was wrong?

02:31.107 --> 02:32.761
- Well, I tried to give her
something to calm her down.

02:32.804 --> 02:35.503
She refused to take it.
- Because?

02:35.546 --> 02:38.767
- She thought it
would hurt her baby.

02:38.810 --> 02:40.812
- You're kidding me.

02:40.856 --> 02:43.163
She's 13 years old.

02:43.206 --> 02:45.643
- Thirteen and pregnant.

02:45.687 --> 02:52.737
♪

02:57.220 --> 03:00.180
[dramatic music]

03:00.223 --> 03:07.448
♪

03:46.878 --> 03:49.664
- It's my fault, right?
I should've been stricter?

03:49.707 --> 03:52.667
- Well, you can't lock them
in their rooms, Mr. Howard.

03:52.710 --> 03:54.364
- Why not?

03:54.408 --> 03:56.540
- Do you have any idea
who the father might be?

03:56.584 --> 03:57.933
- She didn't tell me
she was pregnant.

03:57.976 --> 03:59.717
Why would she tell me
who the father is?

03:59.761 --> 04:01.545
- Did Mackenzie
have a boyfriend?

04:01.589 --> 04:03.068
- Not that I know of.

04:03.112 --> 04:04.461
- Did she ever mention
any boys?

04:04.505 --> 04:05.854
Maybe somebody she went
to school with,

04:05.897 --> 04:07.769
could've been somebody
she met online.

04:09.597 --> 04:12.252
- What do I know about
raising a girl?

04:12.295 --> 04:13.601
You know, it was stupid

04:13.644 --> 04:15.864
to think that
I could replace Angela.

04:15.907 --> 04:18.083
- Is that her mother?
- Yeah.

04:18.127 --> 04:19.607
She passed two years ago.

04:19.650 --> 04:22.174
We were only married
for a short period of time.

04:22.218 --> 04:23.785
[sighs]

04:23.828 --> 04:26.004
- So it's--it's just been
you two alone

04:26.048 --> 04:27.615
for the past few years?

04:29.704 --> 04:34.230
- I know you have to ask,
but come on, man.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.537
[somber music]

04:36.580 --> 04:39.322
I'm a father to her.

04:40.192 --> 04:43.239
- Stepfather.
Did you adopt Mackenzie?

04:43.283 --> 04:44.849
- I couldn't.

04:44.893 --> 04:48.418
She has a junkie father
running around somewhere.

04:48.462 --> 04:51.508
He and Angela divorced
when we met.

04:51.552 --> 04:53.815
Look, the thing is...

04:54.598 --> 04:58.646
I love Mackenzie
like she's my own

04:58.689 --> 05:00.778
and I thought I was doing
the right thing.

05:00.822 --> 05:02.954
- [sighs]

05:04.782 --> 05:07.481
- The doctor at the hospital
let me hear the heartbeat.

05:07.524 --> 05:09.961
It was the most unreal
feeling ever.

05:10.005 --> 05:12.660
- And you didn't tell
your dad?

05:12.703 --> 05:14.836
- Stepdad,
and I was going to.

05:14.879 --> 05:18.709
It's just Garrett is a little
hard to talk to sometimes.

05:18.753 --> 05:20.232
The baby's only
eight weeks old.

05:20.276 --> 05:21.886
- Did you tell
the baby's father?

05:21.930 --> 05:23.323
- He wouldn't care.

05:23.366 --> 05:25.368
- Well, how do you know that?

05:25.412 --> 05:27.022
- I don't want to talk
about it.

05:27.065 --> 05:28.371
Can I go to school now?

05:28.415 --> 05:29.546
I have a math quiz
and it's super important.

05:29.590 --> 05:30.982
- Not quite yet, Mackenzie.

05:31.026 --> 05:34.072
So I know that this is
difficult to talk about,

05:34.116 --> 05:38.773
but we need to know
the details of what happened.

05:40.165 --> 05:44.996
So the first question
I want to ask you is...

05:45.040 --> 05:48.348
were you upset about
how this happened?

05:48.391 --> 05:50.306
- Why do you even care?

05:50.350 --> 05:52.177
I'm old enough to make
my own decisions.

05:52.221 --> 05:53.657
- No one is saying you're not.

05:53.701 --> 05:56.051
We're concerned though and
your stepfather's concerned.

05:58.706 --> 06:01.665
- Listen, we just want
what's best for you.

06:01.709 --> 06:04.059
- Okay.

06:05.321 --> 06:06.931
He was just some guy.

06:06.975 --> 06:08.933
- What was his name?

06:08.977 --> 06:10.413
- I don't know.

06:10.457 --> 06:11.980
I was buying yogurt
in Whole Foods.

06:12.023 --> 06:12.981
We started talking.

06:13.024 --> 06:15.679
It was only one time
in his car.

06:15.723 --> 06:17.768
- So he's old enough to drive.

06:17.812 --> 06:19.422
- You don't understand.

06:19.466 --> 06:21.598
I wanted to; he didn't
force me or anything like that.

06:21.642 --> 06:24.035
- Listen, Mackenzie,
if he was a grown man.

06:24.079 --> 06:26.647
it's not okay.

06:26.690 --> 06:28.953
- So what color was the car?

06:29.563 --> 06:32.043
- It was blue.
A BMW, I think.

06:32.087 --> 06:34.698
- Great, that's very helpful,
Mackenzie.

06:34.742 --> 06:37.092
And what else can
you remember about him?

06:37.135 --> 06:38.876
- Why?

06:40.791 --> 06:44.273
- Because under the law,
Mackenzie,

06:44.316 --> 06:49.278
what he did to you
may be rape.

06:49.321 --> 06:56.546
♪

07:01.769 --> 07:04.119
- Is she okay?
- She's fine, considering.

07:04.162 --> 07:05.773
- Did she say who
the father was?

07:05.816 --> 07:08.384
- She said it's a man that
she met at Whole Foods.

07:08.428 --> 07:09.603
She doesn't know his name.

07:09.646 --> 07:11.300
- That's ridiculous.

07:11.343 --> 07:12.475
- Yeah, I know.
She's--

07:12.519 --> 07:13.737
she's covering for somebody.

07:13.781 --> 07:15.435
- Why would she do that?

07:15.478 --> 07:17.654
- Because she's 13 years old
and this is a lot to handle.

07:17.698 --> 07:21.441
- She'll come around in time.

07:21.484 --> 07:23.573
- Well, and if she doesn't?

07:24.748 --> 07:27.359
- Do you know anybody
that drives a blue BMW?

07:27.403 --> 07:28.796
- No.
Why?

07:28.839 --> 07:32.234
- Mr. Howard, would you mind
taking a look at this?

07:33.627 --> 07:36.368
Anybody here ring a bell?

07:36.412 --> 07:37.718
- Where did you get this?

07:37.761 --> 07:39.067
- Our computer geeks found it

07:39.110 --> 07:40.938
on Mackenzie's fake
Instagram account.

07:40.982 --> 07:43.288
- It's just an account where
she can hide stuff from you.

07:43.332 --> 07:48.729
- "Send nudes they said.
It'd be fun they said, lolz."

07:48.772 --> 07:50.470
That doesn't even sound
like Mackenzie.

07:50.513 --> 07:53.298
- Do you recognize them?

07:53.342 --> 07:55.518
- Well, they must be
from her school.

08:01.176 --> 08:02.612
- This is middle school.

08:02.656 --> 08:05.267
Our biggest problems are
cyberbullying and texting,

08:05.310 --> 08:06.616
not teen pregnancy.

08:06.660 --> 08:08.400
- Well, unfortunately
that's where we are.

08:08.444 --> 08:10.794
Now what can you tell us
about Mackenzie?

08:10.838 --> 08:13.318
- She's bright, popular,
gets good grades.

08:13.362 --> 08:15.103
She never gets in trouble.

08:15.146 --> 08:17.018
- Have you noticed
a behavioral change

08:17.061 --> 08:18.454
in her recently?

08:18.498 --> 08:19.890
- Honestly, no.

08:19.934 --> 08:21.979
She's always been a standout
student, super involved.

08:22.023 --> 08:24.373
Volleyball,
school play, art club.

08:24.416 --> 08:25.722
- Look, uh, is there--
is there someone

08:25.766 --> 08:27.028
that she could've
confided in?

08:27.071 --> 08:28.638
Maybe, uh, a--a close friend
or something?

08:28.682 --> 08:30.335
- I can ask around
but I can assure you,

08:30.379 --> 08:32.642
whatever happened to her
didn't happen here.

08:32.686 --> 08:34.165
- Okay, hey, Father,

08:34.209 --> 08:35.993
I need you to look at one more
thing for me, all right?

08:36.037 --> 08:38.126
These two boys,
they go to school here?

08:38.169 --> 08:39.519
- Yes, of course.

08:39.562 --> 08:41.782
Uh, Logan Larson
and Chase Madera.

08:41.825 --> 08:43.827
- Okay, we're going to need
to talk to them.

08:45.046 --> 08:46.438
- We were at Chase's
hanging out.

08:46.482 --> 08:47.570
His dad was home.

08:47.614 --> 08:49.659
Nothing, like,
sexual happened.

08:49.703 --> 08:51.748
- All right, well,
then tell me, Logan,

08:51.792 --> 08:57.014
why did she write that
you asked to send nudes?

08:57.058 --> 09:00.235
- I-I was screwing around.
I don't know.

09:00.278 --> 09:02.193
She never did send them.

09:02.237 --> 09:03.891
- Did you ever date Mackenzie?

09:03.934 --> 09:05.980
- No. I mean, we're friends,
you know?

09:06.023 --> 09:07.982
- But you thought about it.
- Sure.

09:08.025 --> 09:09.810
I mean...

09:09.853 --> 09:11.551
- Okay, listen,
I know what you mean.

09:11.594 --> 09:13.378
- No, it's not like that.

09:13.422 --> 09:16.338
Mack is just one of those girls
who is always touching you.

09:16.381 --> 09:17.992
- Touching how?

09:18.035 --> 09:20.690
- Like she puts her hand
on yours, stuff like that.

09:20.734 --> 09:23.345
Makes you think...

09:23.388 --> 09:25.216
- Makes you think what, Logan?

09:25.260 --> 09:27.958
- That she wants to be
closer than you really are,

09:28.002 --> 09:31.179
but I never did anything.

09:31.222 --> 09:33.355
- I used to think it was
because she was shy.

09:33.398 --> 09:34.704
- But now?

09:34.748 --> 09:38.012
- I realized she wants you
to lean in real close.

09:38.055 --> 09:39.448
- How close?

09:39.491 --> 09:40.754
- Close enough
to smell her perfume.

09:40.797 --> 09:42.625
It was like blueberries
or something.

09:42.669 --> 09:44.584
- Huh. Did you like that?

09:44.627 --> 09:46.586
- Sure.

09:46.629 --> 09:48.196
I mean, the girls around here

09:48.239 --> 09:49.937
aren't allowed
to wear that stuff.

09:49.980 --> 09:52.113
Most of them follow the rules.

09:52.156 --> 09:53.636
- But not Mackenzie?

09:53.680 --> 09:55.377
- I guess.

09:55.420 --> 09:58.641
- Did you ever get past the,
uh, the smelling stage?

09:58.685 --> 10:01.644
- I tried to kiss her a couple
of times but we never did.

10:01.688 --> 10:03.254
She's a tease.

10:03.298 --> 10:04.908
- Did that make you mad?

10:04.952 --> 10:06.910
- More like confused.

10:06.954 --> 10:09.260
Maybe the whole thing
was an act,

10:09.304 --> 10:13.003
- Or maybe she was
a scared 13-year-old girl.

10:13.047 --> 10:15.136
- Yeah, tell that to Dreyfus.

10:15.179 --> 10:16.659
- Who's that?

10:16.703 --> 10:18.400
- He teaches drama,

10:18.443 --> 10:20.924
but the real drama is
what goes on backstage.

10:20.968 --> 10:23.144
That's what I've heard anyways.

10:24.232 --> 10:26.713
- She's a natural.
Hey, do you mind?

10:26.756 --> 10:28.584
We're having a dress rehearsal
tomorrow.

10:28.628 --> 10:29.977
- Nah, it's all good.

10:30.020 --> 10:31.718
You ever worked one-on-one
with Mackenzie?

10:31.761 --> 10:33.763
- Alone?
Yeah, sure.

10:33.807 --> 10:35.025
I read lines with her.

10:35.069 --> 10:36.636
I do with all the students.

10:36.679 --> 10:39.116
- Maybe a little more often
with Mackenzie?

10:39.160 --> 10:41.684
- Yeah, what with her being
such a natural and all.

10:41.728 --> 10:44.121
- [chuckles]
You're kidding me, right?

10:44.165 --> 10:45.862
I would think a couple
of detectives

10:45.906 --> 10:47.777
would see right through
student gossip.

10:47.821 --> 10:50.127
Hormones set
teenage fantasies flying.

10:50.171 --> 10:52.739
- This may be a little more
than fantasy, Mr. Dreyfus.

10:52.782 --> 10:54.958
- Mackenzie Tolliver
is pregnant.

10:56.481 --> 10:57.744
- She's only 13.

10:57.787 --> 10:59.920
[dramatic music]

10:59.963 --> 11:02.270
Oh, my God.
You think that I'm the father.

11:02.313 --> 11:03.793
- Yeah.

11:03.837 --> 11:06.143
- Is there a reason
that we shouldn't?

11:06.187 --> 11:08.015
- Look, I never touched
that girl

11:08.058 --> 11:09.886
and anyone who says
I did is a liar.

11:09.930 --> 11:12.193
- What kind of car do
you drive, Mr. Dreyfus?

11:12.236 --> 11:14.282
- A BMW.
Why?

11:14.325 --> 11:16.545
♪

11:16.588 --> 11:18.329
- Let me guess, blue?

11:18.373 --> 11:21.724
♪

11:21.768 --> 11:24.031
- Let's go.
- Wait, am I under arrest?

11:24.074 --> 11:26.250
- You can be if you don't want
to come willingly.

11:26.294 --> 11:33.344
♪

11:37.435 --> 11:37.609
.

11:37.653 --> 11:40.047
- I've been at Saint Matthew's
for eight years.

11:40.090 --> 11:41.265
Why would I do something
like this now?

11:41.309 --> 11:42.832
- One of the great mysteries
of life.

11:42.876 --> 11:46.009
- You know, some guys, they--
they just like young girls.

11:46.053 --> 11:48.272
- The younger the better.

11:48.316 --> 11:50.666
- Have you asked around
the school?

11:50.710 --> 11:52.015
I've got a great record.

11:52.059 --> 11:53.625
I've never been accused
of anything like this.

11:53.669 --> 11:55.323
- Well, everybody's got
to start somewhere.

11:55.366 --> 11:57.368
- Okay, okay, you say
that she's pregnant?

11:57.412 --> 11:59.849
I'll give blood, DNA,
whatever you want.

12:01.633 --> 12:04.419
- That's exactly
what we want to hear.

12:06.943 --> 12:08.597
- Absolutely not.

12:08.640 --> 12:10.642
- I thought you wanted to know
who the father was.

12:10.686 --> 12:13.907
- I did, but judging by
the looks on your faces now,

12:13.950 --> 12:15.212
uh, I'm not so sure.

12:15.256 --> 12:17.258
- Even if Mackenzie was raped?

12:17.301 --> 12:18.912
- Look, she doesn't see it
that way

12:18.955 --> 12:20.304
and at this point,

12:20.348 --> 12:22.132
she's decided
she's keeping the baby.

12:22.176 --> 12:23.481
- So what?

12:23.525 --> 12:24.787
So--wait, wait,
you're--you're fine

12:24.831 --> 12:26.658
with what happened
to your daughter?

12:26.702 --> 12:27.964
- I have to be.

12:28.008 --> 12:30.837
I loved Mack's mom,
I love Mack.

12:30.880 --> 12:33.187
[solemn music]

12:33.230 --> 12:34.841
I'm in this for the long haul.

12:34.884 --> 12:37.147
And the last thing we need is
some stranger butting in

12:37.191 --> 12:40.542
and demanding rights that
he doesn't deserve.

12:40.585 --> 12:42.892
Look, this is
what Mackenzie wants!

12:42.936 --> 12:44.851
- Mackenzie's a child.

12:47.331 --> 12:49.290
She doesn't know
what she wants.

12:49.333 --> 12:51.640
- Yes, she does.

12:51.683 --> 12:54.469
And if that changes,
we'll reconsider.

12:59.996 --> 13:02.825
- So the way this usually works
is first, there's a crime,

13:02.869 --> 13:04.131
and then we go to court

13:04.174 --> 13:05.480
and we nail the person
that did it.

13:05.523 --> 13:07.308
- We can't tell
if there's a crime

13:07.351 --> 13:08.831
until we know who
the father is.

13:08.875 --> 13:10.441
- We think it was an adult?

13:10.485 --> 13:11.921
- She won't say, and unless
we can get her

13:11.965 --> 13:13.314
to take a paternity test,

13:13.357 --> 13:14.663
then we won't know who
the father is

13:14.706 --> 13:16.621
and we don't know
if she was raped.

13:16.665 --> 13:18.841
- You realize her attorney's
going to argue some form of

13:18.885 --> 13:19.973
my body my choice?

13:20.016 --> 13:21.496
- She's 13 years old, Peter.

13:21.539 --> 13:23.150
- And then we're gonna get hit
with a heavy dose

13:23.193 --> 13:25.195
of her right to privacy.

13:25.239 --> 13:27.502
- Is there a chance?

13:27.545 --> 13:30.635
Just--is there even a chance?

13:30.679 --> 13:33.856
- As long as judges are human,
there's a chance.

13:35.902 --> 13:39.949
- Hey, Stone got the motion
put on tomorrow's calendar.

13:39.993 --> 13:42.822
- Good for you.

13:42.865 --> 13:44.519
- Well, don't be so excited
about it.

13:44.562 --> 13:47.870
- What I meant was, Liv,
is it's good for you.

13:47.914 --> 13:50.612
I'm not so sure how good
it is for Mackenzie.

13:50.655 --> 13:52.701
- There's a chance that we're
looking at statutory rape.

13:52.744 --> 13:54.485
- There's a chance we're not.

13:54.529 --> 13:57.401
I mean, Dreyfus
offered up his DNA.

13:57.445 --> 13:58.968
Well, what can I say?

13:59.012 --> 14:00.535
It makes my skin crawl
a little bit thinking about

14:00.578 --> 14:02.276
a court violating
a minor's privacy.

14:02.319 --> 14:04.626
You know, because let's say
for the sake of argument that

14:04.669 --> 14:08.891
the father is Zack or Jake or
some other middle schooler.

14:08.935 --> 14:10.371
Why ruin his life too?

14:10.414 --> 14:12.112
- I didn't know a baby
ruined anyone's life.

14:12.155 --> 14:13.374
- You know what I mean.

14:13.417 --> 14:15.376
You know, maybe she--she's--

14:15.419 --> 14:17.291
she's keeping the burden off
another 13-year-old.

14:17.334 --> 14:20.598
Maybe she's being righteous
by--by keeping him in the dark.

14:20.642 --> 14:22.557
- And if it's a 40-year-old
drama teacher?

14:22.600 --> 14:24.689
- [sighs]
I mean, did you?

14:24.733 --> 14:26.213
- Did I what?

14:26.256 --> 14:27.605
- Yeah, when you were pregnant,

14:27.649 --> 14:29.172
did you let the father
know before you...

14:29.216 --> 14:30.478
- Before I what?

14:30.521 --> 14:32.045
- [sighs]
You're making me say it?

14:32.088 --> 14:33.307
We were standing right here

14:33.350 --> 14:35.613
and you told me you
had an abortion.

14:37.093 --> 14:39.313
- I-I never said that.

14:39.356 --> 14:41.576
- So I dreamt it?

14:41.619 --> 14:44.753
- No, Amanda,
what I said was...

14:44.796 --> 14:50.019
is that regret can be
an awful thing to live with

14:50.063 --> 14:53.327
and so you assumed...

14:54.676 --> 14:57.505
- Yeah, and you let me.

14:57.548 --> 15:00.421
- I did,
and I'm sorry, Amanda.

15:00.464 --> 15:03.293
It's just--it's a
very complicated story

15:03.337 --> 15:05.295
and I didn't want
to get into it.

15:05.339 --> 15:06.862
- So it's a privacy thing,

15:06.906 --> 15:08.951
which--which was
my argument to begin with

15:08.995 --> 15:10.605
in this conversation.

15:10.648 --> 15:12.824
All right?
- Okay.

15:13.825 --> 15:16.089
- What the hell?
Mackenzie.

15:16.132 --> 15:17.786
- I'm so sorry, I didn't--

15:17.829 --> 15:19.266
- Are you this Lieutenant
she's yapping about?

15:19.309 --> 15:21.050
- I'm Lieutenant Benson.

15:21.094 --> 15:22.269
- $19.65.
- I'm sorry?

15:22.312 --> 15:23.792
- That's what was on the meter.

15:23.835 --> 15:25.272
Who takes a cab
without money?

15:25.315 --> 15:26.795
- Here.
Thanks.

15:26.838 --> 15:29.885
- A tip would be appreciated.
- [scoffs]

15:29.929 --> 15:31.626
- I hope you learned something,
young lady.

15:31.669 --> 15:33.280
- I'm so sorry.
I was gonna call.

15:33.323 --> 15:34.977
It's just
Garrett took my phone.

15:35.021 --> 15:36.979
- Okay, that's why
we're here, Mackenzie.

15:37.023 --> 15:38.154
Are you okay?
What's--

15:38.198 --> 15:39.460
what's going on?
- I don't know.

15:39.503 --> 15:43.029
I told Garrett
that it was Mr. Dreyfus.

15:46.293 --> 15:48.686
- What did he say?

15:48.730 --> 15:51.472
- He was so upset.
Mr. D's a good guy.

15:51.515 --> 15:52.908
I didn't want him
to get in trouble.

15:52.952 --> 15:54.823
I just thought that,
with the blood test,

15:54.866 --> 15:57.869
you'd figure out anyway
and I'm sorry about the money.

15:57.913 --> 15:59.654
- Mackenzie, where is
your stepfather right now?

15:59.697 --> 16:01.917
- I don't know.
I told him and he left.

16:01.961 --> 16:03.571
- Did he say where
he was going?

16:03.614 --> 16:06.008
- No, he slammed the door.
He was so mad.

16:06.052 --> 16:08.010
- Okay, honey, I want you to
have a seat right here.

16:08.054 --> 16:10.447
I'll be right back.

16:14.495 --> 16:17.454
[police sirens wail]

16:17.498 --> 16:20.457
[tense music]

16:20.501 --> 16:27.595
♪

16:29.379 --> 16:31.120
NYPD!

16:31.164 --> 16:33.383
Mr. Dreyfus?

16:45.091 --> 16:46.309
Mr. Howard.

16:46.353 --> 16:48.790
Mr. Howard,
put the weapon down now.

17:00.454 --> 17:02.586
- No.

17:02.630 --> 17:05.024
- I didn't mean to.

17:06.068 --> 17:07.417
- [sighs]

17:11.030 --> 17:11.204
.

17:11.247 --> 17:14.729
- I was so angry.
I didn't know what I was doing.

17:14.772 --> 17:17.123
Has your blood ever boiled,
Mr. Stone?

17:17.166 --> 17:21.170
She's only 13.
I mean, how could he?

17:22.041 --> 17:24.260
- Please tell us what happened,
Mr. Howard.

17:25.479 --> 17:27.089
- Go on.

17:27.133 --> 17:29.483
- Uh, Mack told me about
the theater teacher,

17:29.526 --> 17:31.615
uh, Mr. Dreyfus.

17:31.659 --> 17:35.924
And I had met him last spring
after the Easter play,

17:35.967 --> 17:38.840
and all I could think about
is his hairy body

17:38.883 --> 17:42.626
on top of my sw--my sweet...

17:42.670 --> 17:44.237
[chuckles]

17:44.280 --> 17:45.760
- Okay.

17:45.803 --> 17:49.851
Um, what did you say
to Mr. Dreyfus?

17:51.853 --> 17:54.595
- I asked him how could he.

17:54.638 --> 17:58.947
I asked him
what kind of animal...

17:58.990 --> 18:01.645
and I told him there was
a special place in hell

18:01.689 --> 18:03.560
waiting just for him.

18:03.604 --> 18:05.693
- What did he say to you?

18:05.736 --> 18:08.435
- [sighs]
He told me to leave

18:08.478 --> 18:12.308
and I said I wouldn't until he
told me to my face what he did.

18:12.352 --> 18:14.702
- And did he?

18:14.745 --> 18:16.356
- He just smiled.

18:16.399 --> 18:18.793
This cruel heartless smile
and he told me to leave again

18:18.836 --> 18:21.404
and I couldn't move.

18:21.448 --> 18:26.322
And I'm so filled with--with
anger, with so much hate.

18:26.366 --> 18:29.717
And he--he pushed me,
I-I pushed him back,

18:29.760 --> 18:32.285
and--and then--
[sniffs]

18:33.721 --> 18:36.071
- And then what, Mr. Howard?

18:37.377 --> 18:39.944
- I saw the trophy.
It was on the coffee table.

18:39.988 --> 18:43.034
I grabbed it and I swung.

18:45.950 --> 18:48.823
And as soon as I saw him
lying there, not moving,

18:48.866 --> 18:51.130
I was filled with guilt.

18:53.828 --> 18:56.961
One sin does
not justify another and--

18:57.005 --> 18:59.442
- I think that's enough.

19:01.618 --> 19:05.579
Obviously he was under
extreme emotional distress.

19:05.622 --> 19:08.277
- I can't go lower than
Man Two.

19:09.539 --> 19:10.584
- How much?

19:10.627 --> 19:12.368
- Two years, one probation.

19:12.412 --> 19:13.848
- You're kidding!

19:13.891 --> 19:15.154
- He killed a man.

19:15.197 --> 19:17.547
- And what jury is
going to convict him?

19:17.591 --> 19:20.159
Thanks but no thanks.

19:24.598 --> 19:25.903
- There's a Mr. Woodward here.

19:25.947 --> 19:27.775
Says it's about
the Quentin Dreyfus murder.

19:27.818 --> 19:29.951
- Send him in.

19:33.520 --> 19:34.738
- Thank you for seeing me.

19:34.782 --> 19:36.653
- What can I do for you,
Mr. Woodward?

19:36.697 --> 19:39.221
- Uh, I knew Quentin Dreyfus.

19:39.265 --> 19:41.397
In fact,
I knew him very well.

19:41.441 --> 19:44.313
- Have a seat.
I'm sorry for your loss.

19:44.357 --> 19:45.923
- Can I get you something?
Water?

19:45.967 --> 19:48.970
- Oh, I'm fine.

19:49.013 --> 19:52.103
Well, like I'll ever
be fine again.

19:52.147 --> 19:55.150
I loved Quentin
and he loved me.

19:57.805 --> 19:59.110
- I see.

19:59.154 --> 20:00.634
- What those people
are saying about him,

20:00.677 --> 20:04.594
that he had sex with
that student, it can't be true.

20:04.638 --> 20:07.031
He wouldn't.

20:07.075 --> 20:09.120
- Were you in
a serious relationship?

20:09.164 --> 20:12.341
- We were going
to get married next summer.

20:13.690 --> 20:17.128
- I'm sorry, you've--you've
caught me completely off guard.

20:17.172 --> 20:18.913
Uh, nobody told me that--

20:18.956 --> 20:21.437
- Of course, of course
they didn't--they didn't know.

20:21.481 --> 20:23.483
Do you know what would happen
to him at that school

20:23.526 --> 20:25.963
if they found out?

20:26.007 --> 20:27.530
- Did you live together?

20:27.574 --> 20:29.140
- I asked him to move in

20:29.184 --> 20:31.926
but he was afraid a student
or a teacher would find out.

20:31.969 --> 20:33.623
- And there's absolutely
no chance he--

20:33.667 --> 20:35.146
- No.

20:35.190 --> 20:38.149
He's never had sex
with a woman.

20:39.238 --> 20:40.848
- His student,
Mackenzie Tolliver--

20:40.891 --> 20:42.502
- Is lying.

20:44.330 --> 20:46.941
I have no idea why,
but she is.

20:46.984 --> 20:49.509
- Is there anyone else
who can confirm this?

20:50.423 --> 20:52.990
- Would my whole family
be good enough?

20:53.034 --> 20:54.688
All of our friends?

20:54.731 --> 20:59.388
♪

20:59.432 --> 21:04.480
Is it--is it true that he was
killed with a bowling trophy?

21:06.265 --> 21:08.223
- It is.

21:09.746 --> 21:12.314
- The West Village Pin Poppers.

21:12.358 --> 21:15.926
It's an LGBTQ league.
That's where we met.

21:20.844 --> 21:24.674
Anyway, I thought that
you should know.

21:24.718 --> 21:26.154
Not that it matters now.

21:26.197 --> 21:29.375
- Thank you.
Thank you for your time.

21:31.377 --> 21:33.379
[sighs]

21:39.515 --> 21:41.996
Liv, it's Peter.

21:42.039 --> 21:44.390
Something stinks.

21:46.261 --> 21:48.307
- Mr. Kayman, the lawyer,

21:48.350 --> 21:51.048
he said that Garrett would be
out on bail before dinner.

21:51.092 --> 21:53.747
He spoke to Family Services
so I could stay home.

21:53.790 --> 21:55.401
- And you're okay with that?

21:55.444 --> 21:58.491
- With my teacher being dead
or that my stepdad's the one--

22:00.319 --> 22:02.799
It was my fault
that he went over there.

22:02.843 --> 22:04.540
It was an accident, right?

22:04.584 --> 22:07.064
- Mackenzie, it's--
it's normal to be afraid,

22:07.108 --> 22:09.240
to be sad, to be scared.

22:09.284 --> 22:11.982
I can--I can help you
find a place to stay tonight.

22:12.026 --> 22:13.941
- No, no, no.
It's fine.

22:13.984 --> 22:15.290
I'm just--
I'm focusing on dinner.

22:15.334 --> 22:16.900
- What are you making?

22:16.944 --> 22:18.337
- Veal chops.

22:18.380 --> 22:20.339
Garrett's favorite.
[chuckles]

22:20.382 --> 22:24.473
- When I was 13, the only thing
I could make was Pop-Tarts.

22:24.517 --> 22:26.345
- Um, my mom taught me.

22:26.388 --> 22:29.043
She used to cook
every night for him.

22:29.957 --> 22:32.046
- You loved her very much, huh?

22:32.089 --> 22:35.615
- I still do.
I miss her.

22:37.138 --> 22:39.358
- Mackenzie, I need to talk
to you about something.

22:39.401 --> 22:41.142
- No, I can't.
Not right now.

22:41.185 --> 22:43.100
- Sweetie, it's important.

22:43.144 --> 22:46.016
I'm not sure that
you're telling me the truth

22:46.060 --> 22:48.279
about Mr. Dreyfus.

22:49.106 --> 22:50.673
- I am.

22:51.674 --> 22:52.936
- Okay.

22:52.980 --> 22:54.503
Well, then, would you mind
telling me

22:54.547 --> 22:57.419
exactly how it happened.

22:57.463 --> 22:58.812
All right?

22:58.855 --> 23:01.945
You said that
you didn't know his name

23:01.989 --> 23:03.817
and you said that you met
in Whole Foods.

23:03.860 --> 23:05.775
- Well, I didn't want
to get him in trouble.

23:05.819 --> 23:07.298
- Well, that's understandable

23:07.342 --> 23:10.432
but I think maybe
there's somebody else

23:10.476 --> 23:12.086
that you don't want to get
in trouble.

23:12.129 --> 23:15.306
- You're clueless.
- Well, then clue me in.

23:19.049 --> 23:21.791
Mackenzie, do you feel safe

23:21.835 --> 23:24.446
when you're at home
with Garrett?

23:24.490 --> 23:27.014
- He's not gonna hurt me.

23:28.276 --> 23:31.497
Wait, you think he put
this baby in me?

23:31.540 --> 23:32.976
- Did he?

23:33.020 --> 23:34.630
- It was Mr. Dreyfus.

23:34.674 --> 23:36.893
Now that he's dead,
I can't even prove it.

23:36.937 --> 23:39.113
- Well, we don't think
that it was him.

23:39.156 --> 23:43.639
And if Garrett killed Dreyfus
because of your lie...

23:43.683 --> 23:46.512
- It only matters if he knows
I was lying, right?

23:53.693 --> 23:55.042
I have to go.

23:55.085 --> 23:56.391
Garrett doesn't like it
when I'm late.

24:00.003 --> 24:01.918
- Well, she's right.

24:01.962 --> 24:04.617
If Garrett didn't know
she was lying about Dreyfus,

24:04.660 --> 24:05.922
he still has a defense.

24:05.966 --> 24:09.578
- My point is--is that
she's in eighth grade.

24:09.622 --> 24:11.580
- You think she wanted Garrett
to kill Dreyfus?

24:11.624 --> 24:14.365
- A teenager? I don't think
she thinks anything through.

24:14.409 --> 24:16.498
But I know that
she's protecting somebody

24:16.542 --> 24:19.588
and my--my gut tells me
that it's Garrett.

24:19.632 --> 24:22.591
- I'll just have to put her
on the stand to find out.

24:24.375 --> 24:25.594
- My Lieutenant and I

24:25.638 --> 24:27.509
rushed over to
Mr. Dreyfus's apartment.

24:27.553 --> 24:29.555
Mr. Dreyfus was on the floor.

24:29.598 --> 24:31.557
He was dead

24:31.600 --> 24:33.863
and Garrett Howard
was sitting on the couch

24:33.907 --> 24:35.735
holding a bowling trophy.

24:38.389 --> 24:42.524
- Was this the trophy,
Detective?

24:42.568 --> 24:44.526
- Yes.

24:44.570 --> 24:48.138
- Huh. I mean this--this could
really do some damage.

24:48.182 --> 24:49.531
- Objection.

24:49.575 --> 24:52.099
- You made your point,
Mr. Stone.

24:55.189 --> 24:57.060
- That's all.

24:57.104 --> 24:59.280
[clears throat]

25:00.934 --> 25:04.503
- When you arrive at
the deceased's apartment,

25:04.546 --> 25:06.417
did Mr. Howard try to run?

25:06.461 --> 25:07.767
- No.

25:07.810 --> 25:11.074
- Did he deny hitting
Mr. Dreyfus with the trophy?

25:11.118 --> 25:13.947
- No.
- Did he say anything to you?

25:13.990 --> 25:16.166
- He said, "I didn't mean to."

25:18.473 --> 25:21.215
- Thank you, Detective.

25:22.433 --> 25:24.261
- Witness may step down.

25:26.655 --> 25:28.570
- The people call
Mackenzie Tolliver.

25:28.614 --> 25:29.571
- Objection.

25:29.615 --> 25:30.746
- She's 13 years old,
Your Honor.

25:30.790 --> 25:32.443
She's perfectly competent
to testify.

25:32.487 --> 25:34.054
- Approach, Your Honor.

25:34.097 --> 25:36.491
- This better be good,
Mr. Kayman.

25:41.017 --> 25:43.846
- [sighs]
- Well?

25:43.890 --> 25:47.110
- Well, this is a bit awkward.

25:47.154 --> 25:49.460
- Objecting without grounds
usually is.

25:50.505 --> 25:52.768
- The proposed witness
is unable to testify

25:52.812 --> 25:55.945
because her communications with
the defendant are privileged.

25:55.989 --> 25:57.599
- I'm sorry, I'm--I'm not aware

25:57.643 --> 25:59.340
of any stepfather/stepdaughter
privilege.

25:59.383 --> 26:01.168
- Neither am I, counselor.

26:01.211 --> 26:05.172
- Yeah, but I'm sure you both
are aware of spousal privilege.

26:06.608 --> 26:08.784
The defendant and Ms. Tolliver,

26:08.828 --> 26:13.746
or should I say Mrs. Howard,
are legally married.

26:13.789 --> 26:16.749
[tense music]

26:16.792 --> 26:19.795
♪

26:19.839 --> 26:22.232
Here is the original
marriage license.

26:22.276 --> 26:24.931
It's from Missouri.

26:24.974 --> 26:28.195
And a copy for you.

26:34.680 --> 26:37.030
- Well...

26:37.073 --> 26:38.858
that's enough for today.

26:43.210 --> 26:44.428
We're adjourned.

26:44.472 --> 26:46.561
[gavel thuds]

26:48.041 --> 26:49.564
- [sighs]

26:53.263 --> 26:53.481
.

26:53.524 --> 26:56.136
- The marriage license was duly
recorded in a courthouse

26:56.179 --> 26:59.226
in Caruthersville, Missouri,
on August 27, 2018.

26:59.269 --> 27:02.533
- It's a year after
her mother died.

27:02.577 --> 27:04.753
She was too young to even know
what marriage means.

27:04.797 --> 27:06.320
- It's bonkers.

27:06.363 --> 27:08.278
Almost 20 states have
no minimum age for marriage.

27:08.322 --> 27:11.455
Over 200,000 kids
were married since 1999,

27:11.499 --> 27:13.066
some as young as 11.

27:13.109 --> 27:15.503
Turns out Caruthersville is a
real hot spot for child brides.

27:15.546 --> 27:16.852
- So this marriage is legal.

27:16.896 --> 27:18.985
- Maybe.
Under the Missouri statute,

27:19.028 --> 27:21.117
a child under 16
can get married

27:21.161 --> 27:23.337
as long as they have the
consent of a blood relative.

27:23.380 --> 27:24.730
- Okay.

27:24.773 --> 27:26.340
Now this consent was
executed by Marcus Tolliver.

27:26.383 --> 27:27.689
That's Mackenzie's father.

27:27.733 --> 27:29.691
- He's a junkie
who's in the wind.

27:29.735 --> 27:30.953
- Right, he was in Rikers,

27:30.997 --> 27:32.215
he did three years
for attempted burglary,

27:32.259 --> 27:33.652
he got released
four years ago,

27:33.695 --> 27:35.131
and then nothing until this.

27:35.175 --> 27:38.352
- Track him down.
Relatives, family, friends.

27:38.395 --> 27:41.224
- She got a, uh, she's got
an aunt in Connecticut,

27:41.268 --> 27:43.096
Penelope Archer.

27:43.139 --> 27:45.098
- Go.

27:46.969 --> 27:48.188
- Why didn't she call me?

27:48.231 --> 27:49.711
She didn't do anything wrong.

27:49.755 --> 27:51.800
Garrett killed that man.

27:51.844 --> 27:53.846
She's moving in with me
and that is it.

27:53.889 --> 27:55.717
- It's--it's not that simple.

27:55.761 --> 27:57.284
- What are you talking about?

27:57.327 --> 27:59.373
I will go to the courthouse
and I will tell them that--

27:59.416 --> 28:01.723
- Um, listen,

28:01.767 --> 28:04.465
she and Garrett are married.

28:04.508 --> 28:05.901
- She's 13.

28:05.945 --> 28:08.904
- Apparently that's legal
in Missouri.

28:08.948 --> 28:11.298
- Missouri.
- Yeah, that's not all.

28:11.341 --> 28:13.256
She's pregnant.

28:13.300 --> 28:15.215
- With his child?

28:15.258 --> 28:17.913
- That's what they're saying.

28:19.306 --> 28:21.177
- Oh, my God.

28:22.396 --> 28:24.877
Oh, that sick pervert.

28:24.920 --> 28:26.879
- Were you and Mackenzie close?

28:29.316 --> 28:31.057
- I'm her aunt.

28:35.452 --> 28:37.977
When Angela died,
I tried to get closer.

28:38.020 --> 28:41.981
I, you know, we'd go down into
the city for girls' trips,

28:42.024 --> 28:44.244
shopping, brunch.

28:45.288 --> 28:49.031
But after a while,
she started to shut me out

28:49.075 --> 28:50.903
and now I know why.

28:50.946 --> 28:53.166
I should've known.
- You can't blame yourself.

28:53.209 --> 28:55.255
- No, she should've
been living here.

28:55.298 --> 28:57.126
It's not like Garrett
was even family.

28:57.170 --> 28:58.737
- Well, speaking of which,

28:58.780 --> 29:00.956
we're--we're trying to locate
Mackenzie's father.

29:01.000 --> 29:02.828
- [chuckles]

29:02.871 --> 29:04.917
Now there's a first class
screw-up for you.

29:04.960 --> 29:07.528
Seems like Angela had
a thing for them.

29:07.571 --> 29:09.225
He went to prison, you know.

29:09.269 --> 29:11.445
- Have you spoken to him
since he was released?

29:11.488 --> 29:16.058
- He came here asking for money
after we buried Angela.

29:16.102 --> 29:18.626
"Pay up
or I'll take Mackenzie."

29:18.669 --> 29:20.454
- So you paid him.

29:20.497 --> 29:22.282
- Christ.

29:22.325 --> 29:23.892
You know, to think
that I thought

29:23.936 --> 29:27.026
Mackenzie would be better off
with Garrett.

29:27.069 --> 29:28.854
I gave him about
five grand in cash

29:28.897 --> 29:31.421
and I told him never
come back here.

29:33.032 --> 29:36.818
And when he's broke,
he just calls.

29:36.862 --> 29:39.386
- So you have his address.

29:39.429 --> 29:41.170
- I have an old one.

29:41.214 --> 29:43.216
Uh, he's not exactly the type

29:43.259 --> 29:45.827
that stays in one place
for long.

29:45.871 --> 29:47.568
[handle rattling]

29:51.398 --> 29:52.616
- Who are you?

29:52.660 --> 29:54.270
- NYPD--I need to talk
to Marcus Tolliver.

29:54.314 --> 29:57.578
- Never heard of him.
- Lola, I need a lighter.

29:57.621 --> 29:59.362
- Shall I introduce you?

29:59.406 --> 30:00.450
- She's a cop.

30:00.494 --> 30:03.236
What the hell
did you do this time?

30:03.279 --> 30:05.891
- I'm here to talk to you
about your daughter.

30:05.934 --> 30:08.763
- You have a kid?
- Oh, shut up.

30:08.807 --> 30:10.156
Did something happen
to Mack?

30:10.199 --> 30:13.028
- Well, first of all,
she's pregnant.

30:13.072 --> 30:14.595
- Just like her mom.

30:14.638 --> 30:16.510
- Oh, that's okay though
'cause she's married, right?

30:16.553 --> 30:17.946
- Look, she said
she loved the guy.

30:17.990 --> 30:19.295
What do you want from me?

30:19.339 --> 30:20.949
- Yeah, I would ask
what you were thinking,

30:20.993 --> 30:22.385
but I don't--I don't see much
of that going on here.

30:22.429 --> 30:24.039
- Oh, you come to
my house to insult me?

30:24.083 --> 30:26.041
- How much did Garrett pay you?
- For what?

30:26.085 --> 30:27.913
- Are you stuck on stupid,
Marcus?

30:27.956 --> 30:31.525
How much did he pay you
to sign the consent form?

30:31.568 --> 30:33.005
Fine.

30:33.048 --> 30:34.397
[handcuffs clicking]

30:34.441 --> 30:36.356
- Okay, okay.

30:37.661 --> 30:39.794
He gave me ten grand.

30:39.838 --> 30:47.062
♪

30:48.934 --> 30:50.370
- They're married?

30:50.413 --> 30:52.763
- Under Missouri law,
it's perfectly legal.

30:52.807 --> 30:55.549
The duly authorized license
is attached to our papers.

30:55.592 --> 30:58.204
- I saw it.
That doesn't mean I believe it.

30:58.247 --> 31:00.336
And I hope that one of you
will tell me why

31:00.380 --> 31:01.947
I don't have to give
full faith and credit

31:01.990 --> 31:04.210
to our sister state's law.

31:04.253 --> 31:06.342
- As noted in our
Motion to Annul,

31:06.386 --> 31:08.910
Missouri Law requires consent
of a blood relative.

31:08.954 --> 31:11.391
It is our position that
Mr. Tolliver was not acting

31:11.434 --> 31:13.915
under his own free will
when he consented.

31:13.959 --> 31:16.483
- How so?
- He was bribed, Your Honor.

31:16.526 --> 31:18.964
- He was hard up.
I gave him some cash.

31:19.007 --> 31:22.097
- How much?
- I don't recall.

31:23.751 --> 31:25.622
- $10,000 is hard to forget.

31:25.666 --> 31:28.930
- And you've changed your mind,
Mr. Tolliver?

31:28.974 --> 31:30.932
- She's only 13, Judge.

31:30.976 --> 31:32.760
I don't know
what I was thinking.

31:32.803 --> 31:34.240
- Okay, Mr. Stone,

31:34.283 --> 31:37.025
I assume that your motion
isn't purely altruistic.

31:37.069 --> 31:38.809
What is your real agenda here?

31:38.853 --> 31:41.856
- Mr. Howard is currently on
trial for Manslaughter.

31:41.900 --> 31:44.772
- And you'd like to call
the young lady as witness.

31:44.815 --> 31:47.644
- The trial is continued until
this matter can be resolved.

31:47.688 --> 31:49.168
- I see.

31:49.211 --> 31:50.952
We'll take a five minute break

31:50.996 --> 31:53.607
and then I will hear
from the bride.

31:55.130 --> 31:57.306
- I think I've always
loved him.

31:57.350 --> 31:59.613
From the first time I saw him.

31:59.656 --> 32:01.310
- When was that?

32:01.354 --> 32:03.617
- When he started dating Mom.

32:03.660 --> 32:05.445
He made us so happy.

32:05.488 --> 32:08.056
He would read me
his books before bed.

32:08.100 --> 32:10.102
His voice was like gold
or something.

32:10.145 --> 32:11.799
I always got goosebumps.

32:11.842 --> 32:15.890
- So you loved him like you
would a rock star?

32:15.934 --> 32:18.153
- No.
- A father?

32:19.198 --> 32:21.113
- I wouldn't know about that.

32:21.156 --> 32:23.637
I've never had a father.

32:23.680 --> 32:25.987
Your Honor, that man
sitting right there,

32:26.031 --> 32:27.336
I don't even know him.

32:27.380 --> 32:29.251
He left before I was even born

32:29.295 --> 32:31.950
and any law that says I need
his permission to be happy

32:31.993 --> 32:34.387
is a stupid law.

32:34.430 --> 32:37.172
And I love him like
a wife loves a husband.

32:38.478 --> 32:42.003
- Like your mother loved him.
- That's right.

32:44.701 --> 32:47.095
- What do you think she would
say about your marriage?

32:47.139 --> 32:48.967
- She'd be happy
that I found a good man,

32:49.010 --> 32:50.142
just like she did.

32:50.185 --> 32:52.013
- You mean the same man,
don't you?

32:52.057 --> 32:53.841
- You don't know anything.

32:53.884 --> 32:57.018
Before Mom died, she told me
to take care of him.

32:57.062 --> 32:58.715
- I doubt this is
what she meant.

32:58.759 --> 33:00.979
- That's enough.
Okay.

33:01.936 --> 33:04.156
A court in the state of
Missouri has already found

33:04.199 --> 33:06.767
that Mr. Tolliver's consent
is valid.

33:06.810 --> 33:09.900
As such, barring fraud,
I am collaterally estopped--

33:09.944 --> 33:12.903
- The father was bribed
to consent, Your Honor.

33:12.947 --> 33:15.558
- Your bribe is Mr. Howard's
charitable contribution.

33:15.602 --> 33:19.214
As I was saying,
I'm collaterally estopped

33:19.258 --> 33:21.912
from finding Mr. Tolliver's
consent invalid.

33:21.956 --> 33:24.872
As such, giving full faith
and credit to Missouri law,

33:24.915 --> 33:28.223
I hold that the marriage
is valid in New York.

33:28.267 --> 33:31.226
[dramatic music]

33:31.270 --> 33:37.232
♪

33:41.715 --> 33:41.932
.

33:41.976 --> 33:44.500
- You're telling me
this marriage is kosher?

33:44.544 --> 33:46.285
- According to Judge Calahan
in the Family Court, it is.

33:46.328 --> 33:49.636
- Ergo Mackenzie cannot testify
against my client.

33:49.679 --> 33:51.725
Because of the sensitive
nature of the relationship

33:51.768 --> 33:53.466
between Mackenzie
and my client,

33:53.509 --> 33:56.643
I move that any mention of said
relationship be prohibited.

33:56.686 --> 33:58.253
- On what grounds?

33:58.297 --> 33:59.689
- Clearly, said relationship

33:59.733 --> 34:01.430
is more prejudicial
than probative.

34:01.474 --> 34:03.780
- Your client is on trial for
killing his wife's teacher.

34:03.824 --> 34:05.782
His marital status
is surely relevant.

34:05.826 --> 34:07.436
- All due respect, Your Honor,

34:07.480 --> 34:09.699
you literally turned green
when I brought it up.

34:09.743 --> 34:12.963
- Truth be told, I'm feeling
a little ill right now.

34:13.007 --> 34:14.487
- That's my point exactly.

34:14.530 --> 34:15.923
A jury will convict him
based on

34:15.966 --> 34:17.751
his alternative
marriage status

34:17.794 --> 34:19.144
and not because of his actions.

34:19.187 --> 34:21.842
- Let's just get this over
with, shall we?

34:21.885 --> 34:23.887
Mr. Kayman's Motion
to exclude references

34:23.931 --> 34:26.542
to the marriage is granted.

34:26.586 --> 34:27.978
We'll pick this up
where we left off,

34:28.022 --> 34:30.851
tomorrow morning,
10:00 a.m.

34:30.894 --> 34:32.679
- Yeah.

34:32.722 --> 34:34.333
Your Honor.

34:34.376 --> 34:36.030
- This is preposterous.

34:36.074 --> 34:39.642
So the law doesn't care
how sick this is.

34:39.686 --> 34:41.862
- Look, bottom line,
to a jury,

34:41.905 --> 34:43.864
Garret's just an irate father
who confronted the man

34:43.907 --> 34:45.692
he thought was sleeping
with his stepdaughter.

34:45.735 --> 34:47.868
- Even though he's the one
that was raping her.

34:47.911 --> 34:51.132
- Yeah, it's not statutory rape
if they're married.

34:51.176 --> 34:53.091
- Bet you thought
you'd never say that.

34:53.134 --> 34:55.963
- Hey, Stone, I looked into
those dates you asked me to.

34:56.006 --> 34:58.096
Mackenzie's first
OB-GYN appointment

34:58.139 --> 34:59.880
was six months
after they were married.

34:59.923 --> 35:01.838
- Which means we can't prove
he married her

35:01.882 --> 35:03.188
just to avoid a rape charge.

35:03.231 --> 35:05.712
- What if he didn't?

35:07.888 --> 35:10.195
- What if he really does
love her?

35:10.238 --> 35:12.762
- Then he'd protect her.

35:15.417 --> 35:17.463
It's worth a shot.

35:18.290 --> 35:21.597
- I want to see them tomorrow
before the trial.

35:23.686 --> 35:26.167
- Okay, we're here.

35:26.211 --> 35:27.560
Why?
You got me.

35:27.603 --> 35:29.257
It's too late for a deal,
Stone.

35:29.301 --> 35:31.738
- I'm considering dropping the
charges against your client.

35:31.781 --> 35:34.001
- Thank you.
- Yeah, no thanks necessary.

35:34.044 --> 35:35.568
He wasn't going to win anyway.

35:35.611 --> 35:37.439
- I'm charging you, Mackenzie.

35:37.483 --> 35:38.962
- What?

35:39.006 --> 35:41.226
- You can't do that.
- Actually, he can.

35:41.269 --> 35:43.358
Mackenzie, you're the one who
put the false idea

35:43.402 --> 35:45.534
in Garrett's head that you
were sleeping with Mr. Dreyfus.

35:45.578 --> 35:47.754
- And it's completely
foreseeable that a stepfather

35:47.797 --> 35:49.103
would take vengeance
against the man

35:49.147 --> 35:51.192
sexually preying
on his stepdaughter.

35:51.236 --> 35:53.934
[tense music]

35:53.977 --> 35:57.242
- Especially when the two
of you are so close.

35:57.285 --> 36:01.420
♪

36:01.463 --> 36:02.943
- Do something!

36:02.986 --> 36:04.379
- Stop!

36:04.423 --> 36:05.728
- Mackenzie, you should know

36:05.772 --> 36:08.253
that your baby will be born
in prison.

36:11.647 --> 36:14.389
- Stop!
- Don't say anything!

36:14.433 --> 36:16.304
- I killed Dreyfus. I had to.

36:16.348 --> 36:17.523
- No, you didn't!

36:17.566 --> 36:19.046
He wasn't going
to say anything!

36:19.089 --> 36:20.917
- You should never have
told him about us.

36:20.961 --> 36:22.615
- He was my friend.

36:22.658 --> 36:24.921
After the cops talked to him,
they told him I was pregnant.

36:24.965 --> 36:27.272
He came to me,
he was worried about me,

36:27.315 --> 36:29.883
but he promised
not to say anything.

36:29.926 --> 36:31.667
- I lost your mother.

36:31.711 --> 36:35.541
I couldn't take the chance that
anyone would find out about us.

36:35.584 --> 36:37.020
- But your marriage was legal.

36:37.064 --> 36:38.805
There's nothing
to be ashamed of, unless...

36:38.848 --> 36:40.937
- I am not ashamed!

36:43.157 --> 36:44.593
You look at her.

36:44.637 --> 36:47.422
How could you not fall in love
with someone so beautiful

36:47.466 --> 36:49.903
and so sweet?

36:49.946 --> 36:52.949
An angel sent from heaven
to bless my life,

36:52.993 --> 36:55.648
to bless me,
and look at us now.

36:55.691 --> 36:59.217
Your stupid laws
have ruined us.

37:00.870 --> 37:05.135
My whole life
I've searched for real love

37:05.179 --> 37:06.311
and I found it.

37:06.354 --> 37:07.964
What was I supposed to do?

37:08.008 --> 37:12.230
- Waiting till she was 18
would've been a good start.

37:12.273 --> 37:13.622
- About that deal?

37:13.666 --> 37:16.146
- Man One, he does 20.

37:16.190 --> 37:17.713
- Max is 25.

37:17.757 --> 37:18.714
- Take it or I'll add
statutory rape.

37:18.758 --> 37:20.455
- You--you can't prove that.

37:20.499 --> 37:22.849
- There's no spousal privilege
when child abuse is involved.

37:22.892 --> 37:26.200
- What jury is going
to believe that you waited

37:26.244 --> 37:28.420
until you were married
to sleep with someone

37:28.463 --> 37:33.033
that you loved so much?

37:33.076 --> 37:34.774
Get this douche out of here.

37:34.817 --> 37:36.341
- No, no, please!
Don't do this!

37:36.384 --> 37:38.386
- Baby, I love you. I love you.
- No, no!

37:38.430 --> 37:40.649
- Listen to me,
you have to let him go.

37:40.693 --> 37:42.912
Let him--

37:43.870 --> 37:47.047
- [sobbing]

37:48.614 --> 37:55.882
♪

38:05.805 --> 38:07.763
What are you doing here?
- I care about you.

38:07.807 --> 38:09.461
- Right, that's why
you ruined my life?

38:09.504 --> 38:11.680
- [scoffs] He killed
your friend, Mackenzie.

38:11.724 --> 38:13.943
He manipulated you.
- I wanted to.

38:13.987 --> 38:16.642
- No, he made you think
that you wanted to.

38:16.685 --> 38:18.731
- You're just jealous.

38:18.774 --> 38:21.081
- Mackenzie,
I didn't know your mother,

38:21.124 --> 38:24.563
but I guarantee you she
wouldn't have approved of you

38:24.606 --> 38:27.609
getting married at this age.
- How do you know?

38:27.653 --> 38:29.089
- Because I know that
she loved you

38:29.132 --> 38:32.875
and I know she would've done
anything to protect you.

38:32.919 --> 38:36.618
Just like I would do anything
to protect my son

38:36.662 --> 38:38.925
and keep him happy
and keep him safe.

38:38.968 --> 38:42.537
Just like you would do anything
to protect your baby.

38:43.364 --> 38:46.324
Honey, I know that this is
hard to see right now.

38:46.367 --> 38:47.934
- Why?
Because I'm just a kid?

38:47.977 --> 38:49.762
- No, honey,
that's a good thing.

38:49.805 --> 38:51.329
That's a great thing

38:51.372 --> 38:54.288
and it's--it's a mistake
to run away from that.

38:54.332 --> 38:56.769
- I'm not stupid, you know.
- I know that.

38:56.812 --> 38:59.380
But you were vulnerable

38:59.424 --> 39:02.296
and Garrett took
advantage of that.

39:03.863 --> 39:05.952
- I took good care of him.
- Honey, I know.

39:05.995 --> 39:10.348
- When he looked at me,
it made me feel...

39:10.391 --> 39:13.133
- Wanted?
Needed?

39:13.176 --> 39:16.397
- Loved?
Like I was a real woman.

39:17.659 --> 39:19.574
- Oh, sweetheart.

39:19.618 --> 39:22.360
But, sweetheart, you're not...

39:22.403 --> 39:25.363
yet.

39:25.406 --> 39:28.148
The truth of the matter is
you should've been out

39:28.191 --> 39:31.456
riding bikes with your friends,

39:31.499 --> 39:34.633
gossiping with your friends,

39:34.676 --> 39:39.638
and Garrett took something
from you that is...

39:39.681 --> 39:43.293
that is irreplaceable.

39:43.337 --> 39:45.426
- My childhood?

39:45.470 --> 39:48.386
[somber music]

39:48.429 --> 39:51.040
- Mackenzie, but what
I can promise you...

39:51.084 --> 39:53.478
♪

39:53.521 --> 39:57.003
Is the way your baby
is gonna look at you.

39:57.046 --> 40:01.007
It's going to make you feel...

40:01.050 --> 40:03.444
more loved,

40:03.488 --> 40:07.883
more needed than
you can ever imagine.

40:10.190 --> 40:13.411
But it's an awesome
responsibility.

40:16.414 --> 40:18.285
- I bet you're a good mom.
- [chuckles]

40:18.328 --> 40:23.116
I don't know.
It's just trial and error.

40:24.073 --> 40:27.120
- At least you didn't die.

40:31.429 --> 40:33.256
- Sweetheart.

40:33.300 --> 40:35.694
Oh, sweetheart.
Sweetheart.

40:35.737 --> 40:40.525
- [sobbing]
- Oh, honey.

40:40.568 --> 40:47.401
♪

40:52.232 --> 40:52.450
.

40:52.493 --> 40:55.061
[dramatic music]

40:55.104 --> 41:02.372
♪

41:21.304 --> 41:24.482
[wolf howling]
